article.headline: UCLA 92, UC Irvine 54
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Noelle Quinn scored 24 points Wednesday night
to lead No. 23 UCLA to a 92-54 win over UC Irvine at Pauley
Pavilion.

Quinn was 9-of-18 from the field and converted 6-of-7 free
throws. She also added seven rebounds and six assists.

The Bruins (3-2) raced to a quick 18-4 lead in just under four
minutes and led 46-27 at halftime.

UCLA scored the first seven points of the second half and
eventually increased the lead to 61-28 with 15:38 left to play.

UC Irvine (0-5) was led by Kirian Ishizaki, who scored 10
points, all in the first half.

The Bruins also had a strong game from Lisa Willis, who finished
with 20 points. It was the third straight 20-point game for Willis,
who has scored in double figures in 22 straight games. Willis
sparked the Bruins early by scoring 10 of the team's first 18
points.

Nikki Blue also added 13 points for UCLA. Lindsey Plummer and
Chinyere Ibekwe had 11 rebounds each for the Bruins.

The Anteaters were held to 27.4 percent (20-for-73) shooting for
the game.
